Rule Learning, Theory. 

The paper discusses algorithms for connecting concepts based on their attribute-value pairs, which is a key aspect of rule learning. The paper also presents a theoretical analysis of the time complexity of the learning models, indicating a focus on theory. The other sub-categories of AI (Case Based, Genetic Algorithms, Neural Networks, Probabilistic Methods, Reinforcement Learning) are not directly mentioned or applicable to the content of the paper.
